    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ V3 analytical queries use define view entity as projection on ◆ A V3 analytical projection MUST be built on a cube view ◆ Consumption happens exclusively via the InA (Information Access) ◆ Restricted measures use @Aggregation.default: #FORMULA combined ◆ Calculated quantities are annotated with @Semantics.quantity ◆ Compared to legacy @Analytics.query, V3 provides stronger | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "with the provider contract analytical_query clause (kernel 7.83+) — they replace the older @Analytics.query: #TRUE approach. (@Analytics.dataCategory: #CUBE); the underlying cube provides the measures and dimensions that the projection selects. protocol — direct SQL reading or Open SQL FROM is NOT allowed. Tools: SAP Analytics Cloud, Analysis for Office, custom InA consumers. with the expression element syntax to define calculated key figures (e.g., ratio, profit margin, year-over-year change). and @Semantics.quantity.unitOfMeasure to ensure correct unit handling across aggregation boundaries. compile-time checks (e.g., verifying that only measures from the cube are exposed, proper aggregation definitions, and correct InA metadata generation). COMPARISON: Legacy Analytical Query vs V3 Analytical Projection View Feature | Legacy @Analytics.query | V3 analytical_query projection ---------------------|------------------------------|---------------------------------- Syntax | define view + annotation | define view entity as projection on Provider contract | None (implicit) | provider contract analytical_query Base object | Any CDS view or cube | Must be a cube view (#CUBE) SQL access allowed? | Yes | No (InA protocol only) Measure restriction | Manual filtering | #FORMULA + expression syntax Compile-time checks | Minimal | Strict (measures, aggregations, InA) Transport layer | Standard CDS transport | Standard CDS transport SAP Analytics Cloud | Yes (via InA/OData) | Yes (native InA) ADT support | Code completion limited | Full syntax check in ADT Future-proofing | Deprecated (still supported) | Recommended for new development SOURCE CODE: V3 Analytical Projection View"
