    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ Class must implement IF_AMDP_MARKER_HDB ◆ Method must be static (CLASS-METHODS) ◆ Parameters passed by VALUE (IMPORTING VALUE(...)) ◆ USING clause declares external CDS/tables accessible in SQLScript ◆ OPTIONS READ-ONLY for query-only procedures | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "WHAT IS AN AMDP? AMDP allows writing HANA database procedures directly in ABAP classes. Benefits over native CDS: ✓ Complex procedural logic (LOOPs, IF/ELSE, temp tables) ✓ Dynamic SQL via APPLY_FILTER ✓ Multiple result sets (when using PROCEDURE, not FUNCTION) ✓ HANA-specific features (PAL, SERIES, etc.) AMDP TYPES: BY DATABASE FUNCTION → Single result set (used by Table Functions) BY DATABASE PROCEDURE → Multiple result sets (called from ABAP reports) USAGE IN ABAP REPORT: \" Call via class name (static) zcl_amdp_simple=>get_details( EXPORTING im_travel_id = '00000014' IMPORTING ex_travel_details = DATA(lt_travel_1) ). \" Call via object instance DATA(lo_amdp) = NEW zcl_amdp_simple( ). lo_amdp->get_details( EXPORTING im_travel_id = '00000009' IMPORTING ex_travel_details = DATA(lt_travel_2) )."
