    "sectionsText": "CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "WHAT IS A TABLE FUNCTION? A Table Function is a CDS artifact that delegates the SQL logic to an AMDP method (HANA SQLScript). This allows: ✓ Complex procedural logic (loops, IF/ELSE, temp tables) ✓ HANA-specific features (Fuzzy Search, PAL, etc.) ✓ SQLScript advanced constructs not possible in CDS KEY POINTS: 1. Parameters are optional (none here — simple case) 2. Always needs a RETURN parameter (structure of output columns) 3. Requires an AMDP class with IF_AMDP_MARKER_HDB interface 4. Static method with BY DATABASE FUNCTION FOR HDB LANGUAGE SQLSCRIPT 5. No extra annotations needed in the consuming CDS view 6. Table functions support JOINs, UNIONs like regular CDS views 7. Multiple CDS views can consume the same table function"
