    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ ABAP Cloud development model requires `#CLOUD_DEVELOPMENT` as ◆ Released APIs are marked with `@ABAP.ReleaseState: #RELEASED` ◆ Clean-core extensibility: SAP's standard namespace (/DMO/, /SAP/) ◆ Cloud vs on-premise differences: `define view entity` is ◆ Extensibility via `@EndUserText.label: 'Custom'` and ◆ CDS view extensions (`extends view`) add fields from customer ◆ Use ADT's system library (Object Explorer > Properties) to ◆ Upgrade-safe custom code means using only released APIs, | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "the language version — only released APIs are allowed. The compiler enforces this at compile time. in the system library (ADT). Using unreleased objects causes a syntax error in cloud projects. is locked. Extensions go into customer namespace (Z*, Y*) via CDS appends, custom fields, custom logic, and RAP BO extensions. mandatory in cloud (DDIC-based `define view` is not allowed); no direct RFC/BAPI calls; no ABAP SQL in OPEN SQL that bypasses CDS; `@AbapCatalog.sqlViewName` is deprecated. `@Extensible: true` on CDS views allows customers to append fields without modifying the original view. tables or custom logic without changing standard CDS — key ingredient of the \"clean-core\" approach. verify the release state of any API before using it. extending via enhancement options, and never modifying SAP objects. SAP guarantees backward compatibility of released APIs. COMPARISON TABLE: ON-PREMISE CDS vs ABAP CLOUD CDS Aspect On-Premise CDS ABAP Cloud CDS ----------------------- --------------------------- --------------------------- Language version Standard ABAP (#STANDARD) #CLOUD_DEVELOPMENT View definition define view (deprecated) define root view entity DDIC compatibility CDS DDIC-based views No DDIC view dependency SQL View name @AbapCatalog.sqlViewName Deprecated — use entity name API usage Any API Only @ABAP.ReleaseState: #RELEASED DB hints Allowed Not allowed in cloud Modifications Can modify SAP objects Never modify — extend only Extensibility SAP Notes, corrections Key-user / developer appends Deployment On-prem S/4, BW, etc S/4HANA Cloud, BTP ABAP Transport mechanism CTS (file-based) gCTS / abapGit / ADT-managed RFC/BAPI Allowed Not allowed (use RAP / OData) Authorization DCL + SU22 DCL + IAM apps Buffer behavior Full buffer control @AccessControl.authorizationCheck Upgrade protection Manual regression Automatic — released API contracts 1. CDS VIEW EXTENSION — ADDITIVE EXTENSIBILITY"
