    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ CL_CDS_TEST_ENVIRONMENT=>CREATE() creates a test double ◆ GET_DOUBLE()->INSERT() injects test data into the double tables ◆ Wrap tests in an ABAP Unit class (CLASS ... FOR TESTING) with ◆ DISABLE_DCL (via CL_CDS_TEST_ENVIRONMENT=>GET_DCL()) bypasses ◆ Test WHERE clause filtering, CASE and COALESCE expressions, and ◆ Integrate with ATC (ABAP Test Cockpit) — CDS unit tests are ◆ CI/CD pipeline integration: execute via RUN_ATC or CL_ATC_API. | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "environment that replaces the underlying dictionary tables of a CDS view with in-memory test data — no real database access. before the CDS SELECT executes. Data lifetime is scoped to the test method / class. SETUP and TEARDOWN methods. TEARDOWN must call DESTROY() to release the environment. DCL / DCLX (access control) during tests — crucial for isolating view logic from authorization rules. calculated fields. These contain business logic prone to error. discovered and executed automatically when configured in the test class as FOR TESTING. Gate the build on CDS test results. TIPS — WHAT TO TEST: ✓ Calculated fields (CASE, COALESCE, aggregation) ✓ WHERE clause correctness (boundary values, NULL handling) ✓ Associations that project fields into the result ✓ Currency/unit conversion logic ✓ @Consumption annotations that affect client behavior TIPS — WHAT NOT TO TEST: ✗ Simple 1:1 projections from a single table (pure pass-through) ✗ Pure annotation changes (annotations do not alter result rows) ✗ Database-internal optimizations (compareFilter, merge behavior) ✗ DCL / authorization (test those via SAML / authorization unit tests) ABAP UNIT TEST CLASS — CDS VIEW TEST DOUBLE"
