    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ #PRIVATE views are INTERNAL helper views — not consumed by ◆ They are consumed by other CDS views (#BASIC, #COMPOSITE, etc.) ◆ Characteristics: ◆ Use #PRIVATE views for: ◆ #PRIVATE is the default viewType if no @VDM.viewType is specified | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "end-user applications (Fiori, OData, Analytics) ✓ Contains shared logic used by multiple public views ✓ Avoids code duplication across the CDS layer ✓ Is not exposed via OData (no @OData.publish) ✓ Named with P_ prefix in SAP standard ✓ Called \"Private\" because they are invisible to consumers - Common calculation patterns reused across views - Data transformation/complex joins used internally - SQLScript-based logic wrapped for reuse - Text retrieval logic for language-dependent fields VDM VIEW TYPE HIERARCHY: PRIVATE → BASIC → COMPOSITE → CONSUMPTION (Lowest) (Highest)"
