    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ Value help provides F4 / dropdown suggestions for fields ◆ Defined using @Consumption.valueHelpDefinition annotation ◆ Can point to another CDS view, table, or element list ◆ Key parameters: ◆ Additional annotations: ◆ The VALUE HELP VIEW (ZPRAC_CDS_AGENCY_VH below) is a lightweight | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "┌────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┐ │ Parameter │ Description │ ├────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤ │ entity │ CDS view providing the value list │ │ element │ Field in the value help view │ │ label │ Display text for the help │ │ additionalBinding │ Additional return parameters │ │ useForValidation │ Validate input against values │ └────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────┘ @Consumption.filter → Defines filter fields for the value help @Consumption.valueHelp → Reference to a specific VH definition view returning only the key + description for the dropdown. It is NOT a separate file — included here for context. VALUE HELP VIEW (for AgencyID): define view ZPRAC_CDS_AGENCY_VH as select from /dmo/agency { key agency_id as AgencyID, name as AgencyName, street as Street, city as City } In production, value help views are often created as separate CDS artifacts following the _VH naming convention."
