    "detailsText": "corresponding database table or DDIC structure — purely definitional. an ABAP class that provides the data at runtime. behaviour, draft, etc.) — without `root` only read access is possible. or `IF_SADL_QUERY_PROVIDER` for plain CDS consumption. sorting, and paging and must return data as an internal table. calling BAPIs, aggregating disparate data sources, or any logic that cannot be expressed in standard SQL. COMPARISON: Custom Entity vs Table Function vs Virtual Element Feature | Custom Entity | Table Function | Virtual Element --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Base object | CDS definition only | AMDP / HANA function | CDS projection view Data source | Any ABAP logic / API | HANA SQLScript / SQL | Same DB table as parent Code pushdown | No (ABAP layer) | Yes (HANA layer) | No (ABAP layer) RAP transactional | Yes (define root) | No (read-only) | Yes (in RAP projection) DDL / DML support | No (cannot INSERT/SELECT) | SELECT only | No (computed only) Parameter support | Yes (CDS parameters) | No | No Association target | Yes | Yes | Yes Use case | External API, BAPI, RFC | High-performance SQL algo | Simple ABAP enrichment DIAGRAM: assets/diagrams/custom-entity-flow.svg"
