    "detailsText": "or XML format directly within the view definition. value as JSON — useful for storing complex data in a single field. for backward-compatible integration with older SOAP services. from a JSON string; `JSON_TABLE` (via AMDP) expands JSON arrays into tabular form. rows (requires HANA XML functions). or table functions that handle the parsing logic in ABAP/AMDP. CDS elements for JSON serialization in OData V4 responses. COMPARISON: JSON vs XML in CDS Aspect | JSON Function | XML Function --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Serialize to format | `with column format json` | `with column format xml` OData V4 support | Native (JSON as default) | Legacy (SOAP / OData V2) Parse / extract | `JSON_VALUE` expression | `XMLTABLE` in AMDP Array expansion | JSON_TABLE in HANA AMDP | XMLTABLE in HANA AMDP Annotation | @Semantics.json.enabled | @Semantics.xml.enabled Integration use | REST / Fiori / Node.js | SOAP / PI / Legacy ECC Performance | Fast (native HANA JSON) | Moderate (XPath parsing)"
