    "sectionsText": "Key Learning Points ◆ Text associations follow the _Text naming convention (e.g., _Text, _DescriptionText) ◆ A text provider view (like I_CurrencyText) exposes language key (spras / language) ◆ The annotation @ObjectModel.text.association: '_Text' on the consumer CDS view ◆ Within the text provider, the text field is flagged with @Semantics.text: true ◆ When the consumer view is exposed, the description appears automatically as ◆ Only the first text element of the provider (based on language priority) is used; | CDS Source Code ",
    "detailsText": "and return language-dependent text data alongside the main entity. and one or more text fields; it acts as the text source for the association. tells the OData runtime to expose the description as a structured annotation. to mark which field carries the actual description text. a property in the OData metadata — the UI does not need to resolve the association. additional text fields are ignored for the @ObjectModel.text.association contract. COMPARISON: Text Association vs Direct Join to Text Table Aspect | Text Association (@ObjectModel.text.association) -------------------------------------------------------------------------- Join syntax | None — implicit via annotation Multiple languages | Automatic — language context resolved at runtime OData exposure | Single property in metadata (auto) Code pushdown | Yes (fully database) Coupling to provider | Decoupled — swap provider without changing consumers Use case | Standard multilingual descriptions (currency, material, etc.) -------------------------------------------------------------------------- Aspect | Direct Join to Text Table (manual _Text join) -------------------------------------------------------------------------- Join syntax | Explicit LEFT OUTER JOIN with language filter Multiple languages | Requires explicit WHERE spras = sy-langu OData exposure | Separate navigation property Code pushdown | Yes (fully database) Coupling to provider | Tight — consumer depends on text table structure Use case | Custom joins or when annotation model cannot be used CDS — Text Provider View (currency text) /* CDS — Consumer View using Text Association"
